08/12/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament on Thursday (December 7th) supported the government's decision to increase the number of Croatian troops within the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan from the current 148 to 300 in 2008. Lawmakers also debated the role of Croatian peacekeepers in Afghanistan. Currently they handle security and convoy missions.
In other news Thursday, the Bulgarian Defence Ministry announced that the United States has officially requested that Bulgaria extend its mission in Iraq. According to the Sega newspaper, the mission likely would be prolonged by one year, with the US picking up much of the cost. (Vecernji List, Sega - 08/12/06)
